## 1. What the arc set out to build

No single opening brief governs this arc; it is a multi-thread day-and-a-half session whose intent is reconstructed from a frozen preregistry, three closeouts, and the end-of-session handoff. Three distinct-but-linked goals.

**(a) Put the dual-arm probe's central claim to an honest empirical test.** The prior offset-comb cluster (Arc 06) left a synthesis doc (`Build_Docs/Reports/dual_arm_probe_offset_comb_findings/…findings.md` L7-13, L54-76) asserting the operational principle: *"ARM-N is valid as an independent reader only when it is set up to read genuinely new data — not a numerically-collapsed restatement of what ARM-W already saw,"* with five operational conditions (path separation, own instrument law, non-diagnostic route, pre-declared selection, ARM-W-derived activation). The `dual_arm_behavior_verification/preregistry.md` (FROZEN 2026-05-17, L3) names the goal precisely: *"behavior verification, not new science… does the dual-arm code do what the synthesis claims it does, on a scenario that actually exercises the claim?"* (preregistry L15) — five pytest-shaped tests V1-V5, one per condition. (high)

**(b) Build the fixture that the verification proved was missing, and run the design-intended pairing.** The v11 closeout (L7-13) states the constructive intent: the v10 probe *"hardcoded `arm_n_operand = arm_w_operand` on the SR fixture, so ARM-W and ARM-N always read the same data. v11 fixes this by giving the two arms different SR four-form channels."* The design-intent recap (v11 L11-20): ARM-W = wide lens (broad range, loses resolution near the singularity), ARM-N = microscope (engages when ARM-W falls below floor); F2 is the natural wide lens, F4 the microscope, handover at β ≈ 0.85. (high)

**(c) Reproduce V3's lifted-singularity audit V4-natively, and separate construction from finding.** The `lifted_singularity_v4_audit/preregistry.md` (FROZEN pre-measurement, L1, L6-7) states: reproduce V3 "consistent lifted 4D conical in every singularity model" via V4-native eval-layer code, *"V3 is reference for what to attempt, not what to copy"* — explicitly forbidding `lloyd_core_nvar` import and the `K_GK/kc/ks/ki` vocabulary (per V3_REFERENCE_LEDGER + REFERENCE_HYGIENE). The novel discipline goal (preregistry §3, L29-47): pre-register which V3 "findings" are **structurally guaranteed** by the lift `F_joint = ΣFᵢ² − X²` (S1-S5) versus genuinely **empirical** (E1 transversality, E2 null-tangent alignment) — a separation V3 did not make. (high)

Two adjacent paper-hardening threads run in the same session and the handoff folds them in: the cross-fixture refinery audit (`task032_cross_fixture_refinery_audit/preregistry.md`) strengthening the paper's Observation 2, and the F4 observability-rule audit (`observability_rule_audit_F4/`) testing whether the rule should be extended. (high)

Net: the through-line, per the handoff title and the synthesis doc, is the **direct operational attack on whether ARM-N reads genuinely new data or a numerically-collapsed restatement of ARM-W** — the north-star Q5/Q6 question expressed at the instrument level.

