**Refutation attempted.** The strongest break is the arc's own falsifier: only **4 of 7** v11 overlap records have genuinely separated float64 operands (3 are float64-identical, `foldreadback_probe0_v11_genuine_separation/closeout.md` L57-58), so the central "ARM-N reads genuinely new data" question is positively corroborated on 4 records, not all 7; the probe stays scratch-only; conditions #3 (diagnostic route) is absent at arms level and #4 (pre-declaration) is honored-not-enforced (`dual_arm_behavior_verification/closeout.md` L53-54, L18). Does this push the honest verdict to "partial"?

